{"event_type":"group_checkpoint_event","schema_version":"2.0.1","date":"2026-04-06 17:42:06","data":{"uuid":"7992ab84-c703-4ccc-ba38-9ff514acf488","name":"Curated Disease Entity","description":"The Curated Disease Entity (CDE) WG will focus on harmonizing curation products related to monogenic diseases within ClinGen’s curation activities (gene/variant/actionability/dosage), as well as between ClinGen and other entities (e.g., Mondo, OMIM). While it is not expected that there will be universal agreement on the identity of monogenic disease entities, or what to call them, this effort will bring increased consistency and a shared understanding of how the monogenic disease entities are defined and named within ClinGen and by outside groups, including the development of a ClinGen preferred disease name (i.e. ClinGen\_Label) for use in Mondo.

This new working group consolidates two prior working groups, the [Lumping and Splitting Working Group](https://clinicalgenome.org/working-groups/lumping-and-splitting/) (LSWG) and the [Disease Naming Advisory Committee](/working-groups/disease-naming-advisory-committee/) (DNAC).

**To solicit help from the Curated Disease Entity Working Group, please email** [diseasenaming@clinicalgenome.org ](mailto:diseasenaming@clinicalgenome.org)","caption":"The Curated Disease Entity (CDE) WG focuses on harmonizing curation products related to monogenic diseases within ClinGen’s curation activities (gene/variant/actionability/dosage), as well as between ClinGen and other entities (e.g., Mondo, OMIM).","icon_url":"https://gpm.clinicalgenome.org/workinggroups/icon/7992ab84-c703-4ccc-ba38-9ff514acf488.png","status":"active","status_date":"2022-02-14T23:47:01+00:00","type":"wg","coi":"https://gpm.clinicalgenome.org/coi-group/7992ab84-c703-4ccc-ba38-9ff514acf488","members":[{"uuid":"53b29d86-7393-4e60-b0ec-11c2594b8b2b","first_name":"Courtney","last_name":"Thaxton","roles":["Chair"],"additional_permissions":[],"institution":"University of North Carolina","credentials":["PhD"],"code_of_conduct":{"status":"current","current_version":"1.0.0","completed_at":"2026-03-10T17:46:09+00:00","expires_at":"2027-03-10T17:46:09+00:00","days_remaining":338},"profile_photo":"https://gpm.clinicalgenome.org/profile-photos/wzKN3T3MzUj0UbaBkhV2DLQjZw6GAfA7w8hxOdBV.png","email":"courtney_thaxton@med.unc.edu"},{"uuid":"88fa8372-a536-424b-831d-1387e109b5f0","first_name":"Emma","last_name":"Owens","roles":["Coordinator"],"additional_permissions":[],"institution":"University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill","credentials":["BSc"],"code_of_conduct":{"status":"current","current_version":"1.0.0","completed_at":"2026-03-10T01:14:11+00:00","expires_at":"2027-03-10T01:14:11+00:00","days_remaining":337},"profile_photo":"https://gpm.clinicalgenome.org/profile-photos/kRn1R5ARZ9gOTrZtYgJvEbC50cjUtvBP2Qm2jLPq.jpg","email":"emma_owens@med.unc.edu"},{"uuid":"87ca0a2e-8f5e-4200-844c-00fafd5bd6bd","first_name":"Jonathan","last_name":"Berg","roles":[],"additional_permissions":[],"institution":"University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill","credentials":["MD","PhD"],"code_of_conduct":{"status":"curre