{"event_type":"group_checkpoint_event","schema_version":"2.0.1","date":"2026-04-06 17:40:24","data":{"uuid":"91623e1e-ca2d-458f-9e61-feb23c948f65","name":"Glaucoma","description":"The Glaucoma Variant Curation Expert Panel aims to develop variant classification criteria adapted from the ACMG/AMP guidelines for glaucoma-associated genes. The current scope of the Glaucoma VCEP is to curate variants in the following two genes:

\- MYOC (OMIM 601652) is the most common gene associated with adult- and juvenile-onset primary open-angle glaucoma (OMIM 137750) in an autosomal dominant manner with incomplete penetrance. There are over 280 coding MYOC variants reported in the literature.

\- CYP1B1 (OMIM 601771) is the most common gene associated with primary congenital glaucoma (OMIM 231300). CYP1B1 variants cause a phenotypic spectrum that also include anterior segment dysgenesis (OMIM 617315) and adult- and juvenile-onset primary open-angle glaucoma. They are transmitted in an autosomal recessive manner with incomplete penetrance. Over 290 coding CYP1B1 variants have been reported.","caption":null,"icon_url":null,"status":"active","status_date":"2022-02-14T23:47:01+00:00","type":"vcep","coi":"https://gpm.clinicalgenome.org/coi-group/91623e1e-ca2d-458f-9e61-feb23c948f65","members":[{"uuid":"532d75f1-2646-470c-bb9f-6e34e556990b","first_name":"Emmanuelle","last_name":"Souzeau","roles":["Chair","Expert","Core Approval Member"],"additional_permissions":[],"institution":"Flinders University","credentials":["PhD"],"code_of_conduct":{"status":"current","current_version":"1.0.0","completed_at":"2026-03-23T06:13:41+00:00","expires_at":"2027-03-23T06:13:41+00:00","days_remaining":350},"profile_photo":"https://gpm.clinicalgenome.org/profile-photos/V8FHoucCMRTBQOzLeBMCJLEPMZ2m8bRwo29PXHWD.jpg","email":"emmanuelle.souzeau@sa.gov.au"},{"uuid":"9f89226d-a5b6-45ed-ae17-55ee6452e863","first_name":"Andrew","last_name":"Dubowsky","roles":["Chair","Expert","Core Approval Member"],"additional_permissions":[],"institution":"SA Pathology","credentials":["BMedSc","PhD","ClinSci","MHGSA"],"code_of_conduct":{"status":"current","current_version":"1.0.0","completed_at":"2026-04-02T02:16:48+00:00","expires_at":"2027-04-02T02:16:48+00:00","days_remaining":360},"email":"andrew.dubowsky@sa.gov.au"},{"uuid":"c72a465a-0846-4eb1-b804-d328d5f16e7e","first_name":"Kathryn","last_name":"Burdon","roles":["Expert","Core Approval Member"],"additional_permissions":[],"institution":"University of Tasmania","credentials":["BSc","PhD"],"code_of_conduct":{"status":"current","current_version":"1.0.0","completed_at":"2026-03-26T21:53:47+00:00","expires_at":"2027-03-26T21:53:47+00:00","days_remain